The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has constituted a campaign team for the 2022 Osun State gubernatorial election slated for July 16. The partyâ€™s National Campaign Council is chaired by Bayelsa State governor, Duoye Diri, while 11 other governors will serve as members, according to a statement by Umar Bature, PDP National Organising Secretary. They are Nyesom Wike (Rivers State), Seyi Makinde (Oyo), Aminu Waziri Tambuwal (Sokoto), Dr Okezie Ikpeazu (Abia), Udom Emmanuel (Akwa Ibom), Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi (Enugu), Darius Ishaku (Taraba), Samuel Ortom (Benue), Godwin Obaseki (Edo), Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri (Adamawa) and Bala Mohammed (Bauchi). Other members of the campaign team are Senator Tanimu Philip Aduda, Ambassador Taofeek Arapaja, Senator Bukola Saraki, Olusegun Mimiko, Senator Samuel Anyanwu, Chief Dan Orbih, Debo Ologunagba, Senator Dino Melaye, among others. The statement said the council would be inaugurated on Wednesday and urged all members of the National Executive Committee to attend. 